h a great choice for busy, messy households. With just a few easy habits, you can keep your rug looking bright and fresh every day.<br><br><strong>Vacuum Gently but Often:</strong> Regular vacuuming helps remove dust and crumbs before they sink deeper into the fibers. Use a light setting and be extra gentle around the edges to protect the weave.<br><br><strong>Treat Spills Immediately:</strong> If water, drinks, or food land on the rug, blot the area right away with a clean cloth. Apply a small amount of mild soap mixed with warm water, then rinse gently and blot dry. Avoid rubbing, as it may push the stain deeper.<br><br><strong>Use the Right Washing Method:</strong> For a full clean, smaller rugs can be placed in the washing machine on a gentle cycle with cold water. If the rug is too large, hand washing is a safe option. Always use mild detergent and avoid hot water or harsh cycles.<br><br><strong>Air Dry Flat and Avoid Heat:</strong> After washing, let the rug dry naturally by laying it flat in a shaded, well-ventilated spot. Do not use a dryer, hang it up, or leave it in direct sunlight, as heat can cause damage or fading.<em><strong><br></strong></em></p></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-98_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gVJwnc hMWwiY pf-99_"><h2 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-gplwNw jqcdAe pf-100_ pf-heading-1-h2"><i class="sc-bHnkpz hbEJPn pf-101_ pf-icon-1 pfa pfa-star pf-lg-hide pf-md-hide pf-sm-hide pf-hide" data-pf-type="Icon"></i>Why Lany Space Rugs Are Perfect for Busy, Messy Households</h2></div></div></div><div class="sc-hzhKNl fltMam pf-102_ pf-r pf-r-eh" style="--s-xs:15px;position:relative" data-pf-type="Row"><div class="pf-c" style="--c-xs:12;--c-sm:12;--c-md:12;--c-lg:12"><div data-pf-type="Column" class="sc-gVJwnc hMWwiY pf-103_"><p class="sc-cTTcKX grRDLS pf-104_ pf-text-1" data-pf-t